Overview
========

This describes the use cases for consuming *notes* and *attachment* events. These events are wrapped in an `attachment` element.

*Please note:* The payloads for both of these events are very similar. The only difference is that a note will have a `description` attribute and an attachment will have a `file_url` element as you'll see in the examples below. Use this for your branch logic.

Event Processing
================

Notes
-----

Note events will have the following payload structure:

```
	{
	    "Payload": {
	        "Actions": [
	            {
	                "ID": null,
	                "Put": {
	                    "attachment": {
	                        "id": 3675,
	                        "entity_type": "Job",
	                        "entity_id": 30463,
	                        "description": "some note",
	                        "updated_at": "2018-05-18T10:14:51+0000",
							"job": {
	                            "external_ids": [
	                                "namespace:your_system_id"
	                            ]
	                        }	                        
	                    }
	                }
	            }
	        ]
	    }
	}
```

There's nothing more to it. Just pick up the `description` and process to your system.

Attachment
----------

Attachment events will have the following payload structure:

```
    "Payload": {
        "Actions": [
            {
                "ID": null,
                "Put": {
                    "attachment": {
                        "id": 3676,
                        "entity_type": "Job",
                        "entity_id": 30463,
                        "file_token": "37f3cf22-f1c5-437c-a078-8608e25a0b2b",
                        "name": "DispatchConnect.png",
                        "updated_at": "2018-05-18T10:15:49+0000",
						"job": {
                            "external_ids": [
                                "namespace:your_system_id"
                            ]
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        ]
    }
```

The attachment is accessed via the `file_token` attribute. When opening this should be prepended with either `https://files-api/v1/datafiles/` (production) or `https://files-api-sandbox/v1/datafiles/` (sandbox).

Overview
========

This describes the use cases for processing *Survey* events. These events are wrapped in an `surveyresponse` element.

Event Processing
================

Survey Submitted
----------------

Survey events will have the following payload structure:

```
	{
	    "Payload": {
	        "Actions": [
	            {
	                "ID": null,
	                "Put": {
	                    "surveyresponse": {
	                        "account_message": "Average",
	                        "account_rating": 3,
	                        "id": 4361,
	                        "job_id": 30459,
	                        "message": "Great!",
	                        "rating": 5,
	                        "updated_at": "2018-05-18T10:57:10+0000",
							"job": {
	                            "external_ids": [
	                                "namespace:your_system_id"
	                            ]
	                        }
	                    }
	                }
	            }
	        ]
	    }
	}
```


The survey `message` is broken up as follows:

* Text in [ ] are the "Tell us why" reasons
* The remainder are the "additional comments"

